## Control-plane install (Atlas-provided)

The Envoy Gateway controller and the Gateway API CRDs it requires are installed
from the upstream OCI Helm chart â€” this tree vendors **no** CRD or controller
copies:

```sh
helm install eg oci://docker.io/envoyproxy/gateway-helm \
  --version v1.8.0 \
  -n envoy-gateway-system --create-namespace
```

- **Chart**: `oci://docker.io/envoyproxy/gateway-helm` `--version v1.8.0`
  (pinned in `.forge/standards/gateway.yaml` `versions.envoy_gateway_chart`).
- **Gateway API CRD bundle**: `v1.5.1` (vendored by the chart; pinned in
  `gateway.yaml` `versions.gateway_api_bundle`). Ships `GatewayClass`,
  `Gateway`, `HTTPRoute`, and `BackendTLSPolicy` at GA
  `gateway.networking.k8s.io/v1`.
- **Namespace**: `envoy-gateway-system` (controller). The data-plane resources
  below deploy into the application namespace.
- **Values**: tune the chart values (replicas, resources, logging) Atlas-side;
  no values file is vendored here.

